msgctxt "an5.193:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.193:0.2"
msgid "20. Brāhmaṇavagga "
msgstr "20. Brahmins "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.193:0.3"
msgid "193. Saṅgāravasutta "
msgstr "193. With Saṅgārava "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.193:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then Saṅgārava the brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "an5.193:1.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, Saṅgārava sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.193:1.3"
msgid "“ko nu kho, bho gotama, hetu ko paccayo, yena kadāci dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā? "
msgstr "“What is the cause, Master Gotama, what is the reason why sometimes even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced? "

msgctxt "an5.193:1.4"
msgid "Ko pana, bho gotama, hetu ko paccayo, yena kadāci dīgharattaṃ asajjhāyakatāpi mantā paṭibhanti, pageva sajjhāyakatā”ti? "
msgstr "And why is it that sometimes even hymns that are long-unpracticed spring to mind, let alone those that are practiced?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.231, sc2
msgctxt "an5.193:2.1"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, brāhmaṇa, samaye kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati kāmarāgaparetena, uppannassa ca kāmarāgassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, paratthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā. "
msgstr "“Brahmin, there’s a time when your heart is overcome and mired in sensual desire and you don’t truly understand the escape from sensual desire that has arisen. At that time you don’t truly know or see your own good, the good of another, or the good of both. Even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced. "

# NOTE: These are, as near I can get, the actual plant and dye names. Note that while majittha is often translated as “crimson” (incl. BB here), it is typically a softer magenta, see image here: http://handprint.com/HP/WCL/waterc.html
msgctxt "an5.193:2.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, udapatto saṃsaṭṭho lākhāya vā haliddiyā vā nīliyā vā mañjiṭṭhāya vā. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a bowl of water that was mixed with dye such as red lac, turmeric, indigo, or rose madder. "

msgctxt "an5.193:2.3"
msgid "Tattha cakkhumā puriso sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno yathābhūtaṃ nappajāneyya na passeyya. "
msgstr "Even a person with good eyesight checking their own reflection wouldn’t truly know it or see it. "

msgctxt "an5.193:2.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati kāmarāgaparetena, uppannassa ca kāmarāgassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, paratthampi … pe … ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā. (1) "
msgstr "In the same way, when your heart is overcome and mired in sensual desire … Even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.193:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye byāpādapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati byāpādaparetena, uppannassa ca byāpādassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, paratthampi … pe … ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā. "
msgstr "Furthermore, when your heart is overcome and mired in ill will … Even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced. "

#. VAR: ukkudhito → ukkaṭṭhito (bj, pts1) | ukkuṭṭhito (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an5.193:3.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, udapatto agginā santatto ukkudhito ussadakajāto. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a bowl of water that was heated by fire, boiling and bubbling. "

msgctxt "an5.193:3.3"
msgid "Tattha cakkhumā puriso sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno yathābhūtaṃ nappajāneyya na passeyya. "
msgstr "Even a person with good eyesight checking their own reflection wouldn’t truly know it or see it. "

